{
  "text": "The encapsulation of DOX within the mixed micellar systems was performed as previously described [CITATION_1] . Briefly, a DOXsodium deoxycholate (NaDC) complex was obtained by dissolving DOX hydrochloride (50 mg) in distilled water (10 ml) and adding NaDC (90 mg) to the solution under magnetic stirring (2 h). Then, the insoluble DOX-NaDC complex suspension was centrifuged (5600 rpm, 10 min, 20\u00b0C, Refrigerated Centrifuge Combi 514R, Hanil Science Industrial Co., Korea), the precipitate was re-dispersed with distilled water (10 ml) and homogenized with vortex (Vortex Mixer Wizard, Velp Scientifica, Italy).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "27034091"
  },
